01/08/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The country's foreign debt reached $25.45 billion, or 80 per cent of GDP, according to a bank survey published Friday (30 July). The figure represents a 32 per cent increase year-on-year, according to Raiffeisen Bank's office in Zagreb.
In other economic news, Croatia's trade deficit widened to $4.2 billion in the first half of 2004. According to the country's statistical office, exports rose by 20 per cent while imports climbed by 25 per cent. Economic growth rose to 4.3 per cent. (UPI, AFP - 30/07/04)
